 <div class="infoTable" id="plurals">
  <h1 class="banner">Plurals</h1>
  <div class="lessonInfo">
   <span class="closeBox" onclick="document.getElementById('plurals').style.display='none'">
    <i class="fas fa-window-close"></i>
   </span>
   <p class="descPg">
    The plural form of a noun is used when you have two or more or none of
    something.

    Normally, you add '<span class="color3">s</span>' or
    '<span class="color3">es</span>' to the end.
   </p>

   <div class="lessonGroup" id="pluralNormal">
    <h2>Normal Nouns</h2>
    <p>
     For normal nouns, add '<span class="color3">s</span>' to get the plural form.
    </p>
    <h4>Examples:</h4>
    <div id="examplesPluralNormal">
     <p>
      book <i class="fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right"></i> book<span class="color3">s</span>
     </p>
     <p>
      name <i class="fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right"></i> name<span class="color3">s</span>
     </p>
     <p>
      chair <i class="fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right"></i> chair<span class="color3">s</span>
     </p>
     <p>
      toy <i class="fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right"></i> toy<span class="color3">s</span>
     </p>
     <p>
      dog <i class="fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right"></i> dog<span class="color3">s</span>
     </p>
    </div>
   </div>


   <div class="lessonGroup" id="pluralAddES">
    <h2>Nouns Ending in '<span class="color3">o</span>', '<span class="color3">sh</span>', '<span
      class="color3">ch</span>', '<span class="color3">x</span>', '<span class="color3">z</span>', '<span
      class="color3">s</span>', and '<span class="color3">ss</span>'</h2>
    <p>
     For these nouns, add '<span class="color3">es</span>' to get the plural form.
    </p>
    <h4>Examples:</h4>
    <div class="examplesPluralAddES">
     <p>
      dish <i class="fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right"></i> dish<span class="color3">es</span>
     </p>
     <p>
      witch <i class="fas fa-long-arrow-alt-right"></i> witch<span class="color3">es</span>
     </p>
     <p>
